wikipedia_page.main: Edward Roy Nesfield (7 March 1900 – 1 July 1987), educated at King’s School, Worcester,  was an English cricketer who played three first-class matches for Worcestershire just after the First World War. Two of these games were friendlies in 1919 against HK Foster's XI, while the other — Nesfield's only County Championship outing — came the following year. His highest score of 16 was made in his debut innings.
